q1.c : The valus of beta0 is greater when compared to the true beta0 value,Value of beta1 is less than the true value of beta1. Value of beta2 is equal to the true value of beta2. Beta1 refers to the change in variable Y when the variable X change one unit. The value of s is the residual standard error which is 0.96.It is less than the true value of sigma square. The p value for beta 1 is less than significance level of 0.001 and the p value of beta2 is also less than the significance level of of 0.001 hence we have sufficient evidence to reject both the null hypothesis at 0.1 percent significance.

Income has a low negative correlation with price. advertising has a positive correlation with sales, price and income. Most of the sales lies between 5 to 10 and mostly has a normal distribution.The values of Urban are evenly distributed for both no and yes when compared with income. Advertising and shelveLoc have a inverse relation. Shelveloc has almost same mean for bad, good and medium when compared with income. Urban plots are bivariate and shelveloc has trivariate plots.

The p values of other variables is less than the significance level of 0.001. we have sufficient evidence to reject null hypothesis at 0.1 percent significance.Shelvelocgood is the most significant variable
